<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-01-13T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-01-13T05:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.672/537: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-01-13T12:00:00+02:00"><hi rend="italic">January 13,
                                        1927—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received January 13—10:17
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. From sources unknown to us, Turkish press is inspired with idea that
                            ratification of the treaty by the Senate is foregone conclusion.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>